hire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Geza, Jeno, Arpad, Attila, Csaba.","Hungarian: variant of   Papp  , meaning ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’. This surname is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Madog","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name, possibly having the sense ‘fortunate’ or alternatively from Celtic <i>aodh</i> ‘fire’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Foel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, composed of two different Hebrew elements, <i>Yah(weh)</i> and <i>El</i>, both of which mean ‘God’ the implication of the name is that the Hebrew God, <i>Yahweh</i>, is the only true god. This is a common name in the Bible, being borne by, among others, one of King David's ‘mighty men’ (1 Chronicles 11:38), and a minor prophet who lived in the 8th century  bc . The name has been perennially popular as a Jewish name; it was also taken up by the Puritans and other Christian fundamentalists. The name has long been in regular use in North America but was uncommon in Britain until the 1990s. Well-known bearers of the name include the American singer and entertainer  Joel Grey  (  b. 1932 ), the West Indian cricketer  Joel Garner  (  b. 1952 ), and the American film director  Joel Coen  (  b. 1954 ). The French form  <b>Joël</b>  is also used in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Madog Foel ap Ieuan was born about 1200, in Abernant, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Ieuan ap Llywelyn, was 32 and his mother, Joan verch Llywelyn Dyfach, was 32. He had at least 1 daughter with Efa verch Madog."},"et":{"ABT 1200–":"umbes 1200–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1230–1309":"1230–1309","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","ABT 1230":"umbes 1230","ABT 1200":"umbes 1200","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1309":"1309","1170":"1170","Pwlldyfach, Aber-nant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Abernant, Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1200–":"noin 1200–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1230–1309":"1230–1309","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","ABT 1230":"noin 1230","ABT 1200":"noin 1200","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1309":"1309","1170":"1170","Pwlldyfach, Aber-nant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Abernant, Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1200–":"environ 1200–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1230–1309":"1230–1309","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1170–Female":"1170–Décédée","ABT 1230":"environ 1230","ABT 1200":"environ 1200","1200":"1200","1230":"1230","1309":"1309","1170":"1170","Pwlldyfach, Aber-nant, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Abernant, Carmarthenshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Madog Fo